1. e4 g6 2. d4 Bg7 3. c4 d6 4. Nc3 a6?! { Doesn't immediately strike in the center, so white has more than the usual KID structure to aspire towards. } (4... Nf6) 5. f4 Nf6 6. Nf3 O-O 7. Be2 Bg4? (7... c5 8. d5 b5!! { Black's only hope is shattering white's structure at all costs. } 9. cxb5 axb5 10. Bxb5? (10. e5!? dxe5 11. fxe5 Ng4 12. Bxb5 Nxe5 13. Nxe5 Bxe5 14. Bh6 Bg7 15. Bxg7 Kxg7 16. O-O $14) 10... Nxe4!! 11. Nxe4 Qa5+ 12. Nc3 Bxc3+) 8. O-O Re8 9. e5 { Black's play will be justified if white allows black to play e5. So let's stop that with e5 beforehand! } 9... dxe5 10. fxe5 Nh5 11. Be3 Qc8? 12. Ng5 Bxe2 13. Qxe2 f6! { Basically the only move to avoid complete disaster immediately. White has a few winning options, but none of them are clean. } 14. Rae1?? { The right idea, but the wrong execution. This allows black to save himself by giving back the piece. } (14. Nxh7! Kxh7 15. g4 $18) (14. g4 fxg5 15. gxh5 Qh3 16. hxg6 $18) 14... fxg5 15. Bxg5 Nd7 16. g4 Ng3?? { In the complicated attack, black falls flat almost immediately. } (16... Nhf6! { The saving move. } 17. exf6 exf6 18. Be3 Nb6!? { Black has counterplay on all of white's tender pawns, and has successfully destroyed white's center. } { [%cal Gc8g4,Gb6c4] }) 17. hxg3 h6 18. Bc1 Rf8 19. Nd5 { [%cal Gd5e7] } 19... Qd8 20. Nf4!! { The knight finally arrives on one of the weakened light squares around black's king. } { [%csl Ge6,Gg6] } 20... Nb6?! { [%cal Gd8d4] } (20... c5!? 21. Ne6 Rxf1+ 22. Rxf1 Qe8 23. Nxg7! Kxg7 24. e6! Nf6 25. Bxh6+ Kxh6 26. g5+ $18 { White wins in this variation too, but it's never easy. }) 21. Ne6 { An octopus arrives on e6. } { [%cal Ge6d4,Ge6d8,Ge6f8] } 21... Rxf1+ 22. Rxf1 Qd7 23. d5! { Black's fianchetto'd bishop is good, but white's e6 knight is better. } 23... c6 24. Nxg7 { White finally cashes in. But only because the tactics justify the complete destruction of black's king. } 24... Kxg7 (24... cxd5 { Black's best try. } 25. Bxh6 Nxc4 26. b3 Nb6 27. e6 Qd6 28. Qf2 { But it's hopeless as well. }) 25. Rf7+! { One of many winning moves, but it's the most fantastic. } (25. d6?! exd6) (25. e6 Qd6 26. Rf7+ Kh8 27. Qe3! { The cleanest victory. Forced mate to follow. }) 25... Kg8 (25... Kh8 26. Qd2 { [%cal Gd2h6] } 26... g5 27. Qd3 $18) 26. Qe4 { The white queen will not be denied the g6 square. } 26... Kxf7 27. e6+ Ke8 28. Qxg6+ Kd8 29. exd7 Kxd7 30. Qe6+ Kd8 31. dxc6 bxc6 32. Qxc6 Rb8 33. Bf4 { And black is forced to leave the game due to the unstoppable Bc7+, Qxb6+, or Bxb8. } *


