1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. f3!? { The dreaded fantasy variation! I know no theory here except... } 3... dxe4 (3... Qb6) (3... g6) 4. fxe4 e5 5. Nf3 Bg4 { ... up to here, where I have no idea what's going on. The rest of the game is me just winging it. } 6. Bc4! Nd7 (6... Bxf3?? 7. Qxf3 Qxd4 8. Qxf7+ $18) 7. O-O (7. dxe5 Bxf3 8. Qxf3 Nxe5! { Defense and attack. This knight does everything. } { [%cal Ge5f3,Ge5c4,Ge5f7] }) 7... Ngf6 8. c3 (8. dxe5 Nxe4 { This was my first idea, but it loses to } (8... Qb6+! 9. Kh1 Nxe5 $10) 9. Qe2 { [%cal Ge4c5] } 9... Nec5 10. Bxf7+ Kxf7 11. Ng5+ Kg8 12. Qc4+ $18) 8... Bd6 { Forced. Black needs to castle ASAP. } 9. Qb3 O-O 10. Qxb7 Nb6 (10... exd4 11. cxd4 Nb6 12. Bb3 Nxe4 13. Qxc6?? Bxf3 14. Rxf3 Rc8! { A forced line in which black is winning, for a change! }) 11. Bb3!? { The bishop is definitely on a killer diagonal. White is willing to give up e4 in order for more activity. } (11. Bd3 Bxf3 12. Rxf3 exd4 13. cxd4 { The line I was expecting. I missed the killer shot though: } 13... Ng4!! 14. h3 Bh2+ 15. Kh1 (15. Kf1 Qxd4 16. hxg4 Qg1+ 17. Ke2 Qxg2+ 18. Rf2 Qxg4+ 19. Kd2 Qg1 $19) 15... Qxd4 $19) 11... Bxf3 12. Rxf3 exd4 13. Bg5? { Caught me off guard, but then I spotted a tactical shot. } (13. cxd4 Nxe4 14. Bxf7+?? Kh8 { The initial line I was calculating. } 15. Nc3 Qh4! { Black goes on the attack with the open f file! }) 13... Bxh2+! 14. Kh1 (14. Kxh2 Ng4+ 15. Kg1 Qxg5 16. Qxc6 Qc1+ $19) 14... Be5 15. Qxc6 Rc8 16. Qb5 Qd6 17. cxd4 Qxd4?! { I played this after 5 minutes thought with exactly one purpose in mind. Taking on e4, and attacking white's king. } (17... Bxd4 { Black still holds a slight advantage here. } 18. Nc3 Rc5 19. Bxf6 Bxf6) 18. Nc3 Nxe4?? (18... Nbd7 19. Raf1 h6 20. Bh4 Qc5 21. Qe2 Rce8 22. Rf5 $10) 19. Nxe4 (19. Be3 Nxc3! { [%cal Gc3b5] }) (19. Rd3 Nf2+!) 19... Qxe4 (19... h6!? 20. Bf4 Qxe4 21. Qxe5 $18 { White still wins. }) 20. Re3 { Black resigned. Amazingly, with white's king so exposed, there's no possible way to take advantage of it or the loose pieces on g5 or a1. } 20... Bxb2 (20... Qg4 21. Qxe5 Nc4 22. Bxc4 Rxc4 23. Rae1 $18 { Nothing to play for here either. }) 21. Rxe4 Bxa1 22. Be7 *


