1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 d5 4. Bd3 c5 5. b3 Nc6 6. O-O Bd6 7. Bb2 O-O 8. Nbd2 { Not the most common move, but I think certainly the best move objectively. Seeking to saddle white with a locked-in bad bishop on b2. } 8... cxd4! 9. exd4 (9. Nxd4 e5 $17) 9... b6 10. Re1 Bb7 11. Ne5 Nb4 { Poking at the good bishop on d3 staring at my king. This maneuver is short-lived though. } 12. Bf1 Rc8 13. c3 Nc6 14. f4 Ne7 { [%cal Ge7f5] } 15. c4?! { While it works for now, c4 can't be objectively best because it's saddling white with either hanging pawns that are already coming under fire or an isolated pawn as in the game. } 15... Nc6!? { [%cal Gc6b4,Gc6d4] } (15... Nf5! 16. g4 { The scary move that dissuaded me from going in this direction. } 16... Nh4 { Amazingly, the knight on h4 is safe from all attacks for the foreseeable future. } { [%cal Ge1e3,Ge3h3] } 17. Re3 Ng6 18. g5 Ne4 $17) 16. Rc1 dxc4 17. Ndxc4 (17. bxc4 h6 18. Ndf3 Bb4 $10) 17... Bb8 (17... Bb4! 18. Re2 b5! 19. a3 Be7 20. Ne3 Qb6 $15 { [%cal Gb6d4,Gc6d4,Gf8d8,Gd8d4] }) 18. a3 Qd5 19. Qf3? Qxf3 20. Nxf3 Rfd8 { [%cal Gc6d4,Gd8d4] } (20... Bxf4 { How did I miss this... }) 21. Nfe5? Nxd4 22. Bxd4 Rxd4 23. Red1 Rcd8 24. Rxd4 Rxd4 25. g3 g6 26. Kf2 Kg7 { Getting out of all back-rank checks, so my b7 bishop is free. } 27. Ke3 Rd8 28. Bd3 Nd5+ 29. Ke2 h5 30. h3 h4!! { Black tears down white's pawn } { [%cal Gd5f4,Gf4e2,Gf4d3] } *


