1. d3 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 { We've basically entered a reverse Scandinavian where black had to play Nc6 instead of d5. } 4... Nf6 5. Nxc6 bxc6 (5... dxc6 6. Qxd8+ Kxd8 $10) 6. g3 Bc5 7. Bg2 O-O 8. Bf4? { While the bishop looks good here, it's actually not hitting anything and soon time becomes an issue. } { [%csl Gf4] } 8... Rb8 { [%csl Gb2] } 9. b3 Ba6 { [%csl Ge2] } 10. O-O Re8 { [%csl Ge2] } 11. Nc3 Bb4 { Forceably winning a pawn. } 12. Bd2 d5 { I felt my bishop pair was stronger than just winning a pawn, so I decided not to simplify. } (12... Bxc3 13. Bxc3 Bxe2 { But in retrospect this doesn't just win a pawn, this wins an exchange as well. }) 13. Re1 Qe7 (13... h5 14. Bf3 h4 15. e4 d4 16. Na4 Qe7) 14. Bf3 h5 15. e4 d4 { Trying to strive for a better position, rather than an equal one, I over-press here. } 16. Na4! { [%cal Gd1h5] } 16... h4 17. Bxb4 Rxb4 18. a3! { And my rook is essentially trapped. I'm losing the d pawn and losing the position quickly, so I look to complicate matters further. } 18... Rb5!? { [%cal Gd1d4] } (18... Rbb8 19. Qxd4 Rbd8 20. Qxa7 $16) 19. Qd3?? (19. Qxd4 Re5 $16) 19... Rf5! { [%cal Ge4f5,Gd3a6,Ge1e7] } 20. Qxa6? (20. exf5?? Qxe1+ 21. Rxe1 Rxe1+ 22. Kg2 Bxd3 23. cxd3 $19) (20. Qd1!! { The cold, computer defense. Just defend all threats and eventually black's bad position will catch up to him. }) 20... Rxf3 21. Kg2 { A blunder, but a completely human one. } { [%cal Gf6e4] } 21... Nxe4!! { Now black sacrifices a full rook just to get a huge attack. } (21... h3+? 22. Kxf3 Qe6 { [%cal Ge6g4] } 23. Ke2! $16 Qg4+ (23... Qxe4+ 24. Kd1) 24. Kd2) 22. Qxc6?? { White falls apart, but there was no defense. } (22. Kxf3 { Taking the rook gets mated in every variation. } 22... Qf6+ { [%cal Gf6f2] } 23. Kg4 (23. Kg2 Qxf2+ 24. Kh3 Qf5+ 25. g4 (25. Kg2 h3+ { [%csl Gf2,Gf1,Bg1,Bh1] } 26. Kh1 (26. Kg1 Qf2+ 27. Kh1 Qg2#) 26... Qf3+ 27. Kg1 Qg2#) 25... Qf3+ 26. Kxh4 g5+ 27. Kh5 Qh3#) (23. Ke2 Nxf2+ (23... Qxf2+ 24. Kd1 Qd2#) 24. Kf1 Ng4+ 25. Kg2 Qf2+ 26. Kh3 Qxh2+ 27. Kxg4 Qxg3+ 28. Kh5 g6+ 29. Kh6 Qf4#) 23... Nxf2+ { [%cal Ge4f2] } 24. Kh5 Qh6#) (22. Qf1 Qf6 { Simple and easy win if white doesn't take the rook immediately, even with the best defense. } (22... Rxf2+ 23. Qxf2 Nxf2)) 22... Rxf2+ 23. Kh3 hxg3 24. Rxe4 Qxe4 { White resigned here rather than continue play down a king. } *


