1. e4 Nc6 2. Nf3 f5 3. exf5 d5 4. d4 Bxf5 5. Bf4 (5. Bb5!? { The supposed improvement according to the engine. I didn't love this because of: } 5... e6 6. O-O (6. Ne5! { [%csl Gc6] } 6... Ne7 7. Bg5 { [%cal Gg5d8,Gb5e8] } 7... Qd6 8. c4 dxc4 9. Nc3 a6 10. Nxc4 $16) 6... Nf6 7. Re1 a6 8. Bxc6+ bxc6 9. c3 c5 { Where I felt black could easily challenge my center with the two c5 breaks. However the engine improvement is quite nice }) 5... e6 6. Bd3 Bg4 7. c3 Bd6 8. Bg3 Nf6 9. O-O O-O 10. Nbd2 Nh5 11. Qc2 h6 12. Bh7+ (12. Rae1!) 12... Kh8 13. Rfe1?! { It's the wrong rook! The pressure on f2 ends up being considerable later in the game. } 13... Nf4! { I was only expecting Nxg3 hxg3 with pressure on the f file to come. } (13... Nxg3 14. hxg3 Qf6 $10) 14. Nh4 { [%cal Gh4g6] } 14... Qf6 15. Bxf4 Qxh4 (15... Bxf4? 16. Ng6+ Kxh7 17. Nxf8+ Kg8 18. Nd7 $16) 16. Bg3 Qf6 17. Nf1 e5! { Liquidating his backward pawn and showing that black has more than equalized. } 18. dxe5 Nxe5 19. Ne3 Be6 20. Rad1 c6?! (20... Rae8! { White just doesn't have any more constructive moves in this position. }) 21. Bd3 Rae8 (21... Nxd3 22. Qxd3 (22. Rxd3 Bc5! { [%cal Gc5e3,Ge6f5] } 23. Rd2 Rae8 $15) 22... Bxg3 23. fxg3 Qf2+ 24. Kh1 Qxb2 $17) 22. Bf1 Bb8 23. c4? dxc4? (23... d4 24. Rxd4 Nf3+ 25. gxf3 Qxd4 { I was already ready to sacrifice the exchange in order to liquidate, but ultimately this doesn't give white any respite from the f file pressure. }) 24. Nxc4 Bd5 25. Nxe5 Bxe5 26. Bxe5 Rxe5 27. Rxe5 Qxe5 $10 28. b3 Qg5 29. Qc5 Rf3 30. Qxa7 Rh3 31. Qa8+ Kh7 32. Qxb7 Rh5 { Here I lost on time, but the most I had "sealed" was Bd3+ } 33. Bd3+ Kh8 (33... Kg8 34. Qb8+ Kf7 35. Qc7+ $18 { His king is ultimately weaker than mine. I can always play h3 or g3 if absolutely necessary to handle any pressure, and my passed a pawn should simply win the game from here. }) 34. Qc8+ Bg8 35. Bc4 $18 *


