1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. h4 h5 5. Bd3 Bxd3 6. Qxd3 e6 7. Bg5 Qb6 8. Nd2 Be7 (8... c5 9. c4 { The mainline I know }) 9. Ngf3 Nd7 10. O-O O-O-O? { Logical, but it walks directly into my incoming pawn storm. } 11. c4 f6 12. exf6 (12. Bf4 fxe5 13. Nxe5 Nxe5 14. Bxe5 Bf6 { I didn't believe this position for white, but the engine spots out a great resource: } 15. c5 Qa6 16. Qh3! $16 { [%cal Gh3c8] }) 12... gxf6 13. Bf4 Nh6 14. Rfe1 e5 15. dxe5?! (15. cxd5! exf4 16. Nc4 Qb5 17. dxc6! Qxc6 18. Rxe7 $18) 15... Ng4! { I'll admit I didn't see this move at all. Thankfully I have a somewhat convenient defense... } 16. Bg3 (16. cxd5?? Qxf2+ 17. Kh1 Qxe1+! 18. Nxe1 Nf2+ 19. Kh2 Nxd3) 16... fxe5 (16... Ndxe5 17. Nxe5 fxe5 18. cxd5 Rxd5 19. Qc2 Bc5 20. Nf3 $14 { White has to win this game all over again. }) 17. cxd5 Bc5 18. Re2 Rhg8 19. Nc4 Qb5 20. dxc6 Qxc6 21. Rc1 Qe6?? (21... b5!? { An interesting try to take advantage of my undefended rook, but there's simply no way it would work with the black king so exposed. } 22. Nd6+ Kc7 23. Nd4!! exd4 (23... Bxd4 24. Nxb5+) 24. Nf7+ Kc8 25. Nxd8 Kxd8 26. b4 $18) 22. Ncxe5! (22. b4 { The easier move that I felt had to be winning... } 22... Be7 23. Ncxe5+ Kb8 24. Nxd7+ { And indeed - there's a crush if black isn't careful. }) 22... Ndxe5 23. Rxc5+ Kb8 (23... Nc6 24. Qxd8+ Rxd8 25. Rxe6 $18) 24. Nxe5!! Nxe5 (24... Rxd3 25. Nxd3+ { [%cal Gg3b8] } 25... Ka8 (25... Ne5 26. Rcxe5 Qc8 27. Re8+) 26. Rxe6) 25. Rcxe5 Rxd3 26. Rxe6+ Kc8 { Black resigned rather than face the following crush: } 27. Rc2+ Kd7 28. Rh6 { [%cal Gc2c7] } *


