1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 O-O 5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 c5 7. a3?! (7. dxc5 Na6 8. a3 Bxc3+ 9. Qxc3 Nxc5 $10) 7... Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 Nc6 9. d5 Ne5 10. e4 Ng6 11. Bg3 (11. Bxf6 Qxf6 12. Bd3 Ne5 { Black has a more flexible position now that white traded off the bishop pair }) 11... d6 12. Bd3 e5 { A move I didn't want to make, as it now makes the center more less flexible. However, this pawn structure locks down white's bishop and ensures my light squared bishop will be the king of the entire board. } 13. Ne2 Nh5 14. O-O Qg5 15. a4 Nhf4 16. Bxf4 Nxf4? (16... exf4! { I missed this. It creates the threat of f3, and also allows my knight to head for the e5 square. } 17. f3 Ne5 $17 { [%cal Gf7f5] }) 17. Nxf4 exf4!? (17... Qxf4 $10 { I didn't see how I would ever break through in this position }) 18. Qd2 Bh3 19. f3 f5? 20. Kh1 (20. e5! dxe5 21. Kh1 e4 22. Bc2 $16 { And black's bishop is trapped. }) 20... fxe4! 21. fxe4 (21. gxh3 exd3 22. Qxd3 Rae8 $17) 21... Bg4 22. h3 Bh5 23. Rab1 Rf7 (23... Qg3 24. Be2 f3 25. Bxf3 Rxf3! { The move I missed. } 26. Rxf3 Bxf3 27. gxf3 Qxh3+ 28. Qh2 Qxf3+ 29. Qg2 Qxc3 $19) 24. Be2 Bg6 { No trades. My bishop is much better than his defensive-only piece. } 25. Bf3 Re8 26. Rfe1 Rfe7 27. Qe2?! { Walks into pins along the e file, allowing my bishop to remaneuver to a better diagonal } 27... Bf5! 28. Qd3 Qg6 (28... Qg3 29. Be2 Bxe4! { Missed... I thought I had to trade queens first } (29... Qxd3? 30. Bxd3 Bxe4 31. Bxe4 Rxe4 32. Rxe4 Rxe4 33. Rxb7 { A position I kept evaluating as drawn as we shall soon see. })) 29. Re2 Bc8! { Keeps winning chances alive with kingside sacrifices coming. } (29... Bxe4? 30. Bxe4 Rxe4 31. Rxe4 Qxe4 (31... Rxe4) 32. Qxe4 Rxe4 33. Rxb7 Rxc4 (33... a5! 34. Ra7 Rxc4 35. Rxa5 Kf7! 36. Ra6 Ke7 37. Ra7+ Kf6 38. Rd7 Ke5 $19 { And black can win }) 34. Rxa7 Rxc3 35. Rd7 Ra3 36. Rxd6 Rxa4 { I evaluated this position as drawn. However, I missed the best move earlier! }) (29... Rxe4! { The exchange sacrifice I wanted to play... } 30. Bxe4 Bxe4 31. Rxe4 { But here I saw they could sacrifice back for that same "equal" endgame I misevaluated. }) 30. Rbe1 Re5 31. Qd2 Qg3 { [%cal Gc8h3] } 32. a5?? (32. Rf1 { Forced. White needs to handle the possible Bxh3 line }) 32... Bxh3 33. gxh3?! (33. Kg1 { White is still fighting, but this is obviously dead. }) 33... Qxf3+ 34. Rg2 Rh5! { Keeps more pieces on the board for the ensuing attack! } (34... Rxe4 35. Rxe4 Rxe4 { Should still be winning, but after Kg1, there's still no breakthrough. }) 35. Rg1 { Knowing he was dead, my opponent resigned by self-mating. } 35... Rxh3# *


