1. e4 f6?? { I thought my opponent was a complete beginner, so we would transpose to the Damiano, and I would win in <10 moves... } 2. Nf3 Kf7?? { Alright it's one of those people. } (2... e5 3. Nxe5 fxe5?? 4. Qh5+ $18) 3. d4 c6 4. Nc3 (4. c4?! { One year ago, I would have gone for something like this - taking control of the entire center. Now I understand it's more important to dissolve the entire center than control it when fighting against someone like this. }) 4... d5 5. Bd3 e6 6. Be3 Be7 7. Qd2 g5? { Practically speaking this makes no sense. Moving pawns in front of your king is just going to make the attack come even quicker. White should certainly be winning now. } 8. O-O-O g4 9. Ng1 a6 10. h3! { One of the kingside files will be opened by force. } 10... gxh3 (10... g3!? 11. fxg3 { But now the assault would begin on the semi-open f file. }) 11. Nxh3 b5 12. Nf4 e5!? { Suicidal, although the engine thinks this is the best move. Opening up the center has to favor the side who's better developed. } 13. dxe5 fxe5 14. Nfxd5! { Calling black's bluff completely. "You don't deserve to gain any tempi on me." } (14. Nfe2? d4 { Don't give black the opportunity to keep it all closed. }) 14... cxd5 15. exd5 Nf6 16. f4!? (16. Qe2 b4 17. Ne4 $18 { The engine line. I considered this, but I didn't want to trade any pieces here. However, the point is Qh5+ is going to hurt if I can remove the knight from f6. Otherwise, Ng5+ is going to hurt. }) 16... b4 (16... e4 17. Nxe4 Qxd5 18. Nxf6 Bxf6 19. Bg6+ $18 { [%cal Gd2d5] }) 17. fxe5! bxc3 18. e6+! { With this move, I've now sacrificed a second piece, but it's clear black will be mated soon due to the open lines and my active pieces. Black is essentially defending with a single knight. } (18. Qf2 $18 { An alternative that doesn't lose any more pieces. }) 18... Kg8 { Black is up two pieces, but hopelessly lost. } (18... Bxe6 19. dxe6+ Kxe6 20. Bc4+ $18 { An even more immediate knockout. }) 19. Qf2 { [%csl Gh8,Gc8,Gb8,Ga8] } 19... cxb2+ 20. Kb1 { [%cal Gf2f7] } 20... Qf8?? (20... Ng4?? 21. Qf7#) (20... h5!? { The last chance from black to not die immediately, keeping my bishop off of h6, but it's still hopelessly lost. } 21. Qg3+ Ng4 22. Rxh5! Rxh5 23. Qxg4+ Rg5 24. Bh7+! Kh8 25. Bd4+ Bf6 26. Qxg5 $18 { A sample brutal variation. }) 21. Bh6 { If the queen moves, Qg3->g7 is unstoppable mate. } 21... Ng4 22. Qg3 { My threats are not going anywhere, and now the knight cannot be saved. The queen cannot stay on the f file, defending the knight. } { [%csl Rf5,Rf4,Rf3] } 22... Qxh6 { Desperation. } 23. Rxh6 Kf8 (23... Kg7 24. Qxg4+ Kxh6 25. Rh1+ $18 { Ye olde staircase mate. }) 24. Qxg4 Bb7 25. Bg6! { No running! } { [%csl Ge8] } 25... Bd6 (25... hxg6 26. Qxg6 { [%csl Ge8] } 26... Rxh6 27. Qf7#) 26. Qf5+ { My opponent resigned here rather than face the following forced checkmate. } 26... Ke7 27. Qg5+! { [%cal Gg5d8,Gg6e8,Ge6d7] } 27... Kf8 28. Qf6+ Kg8 29. Qf7# *


